In article <33g5vt$p7h@darkstar.UCSC.EDU>,
Darrell Long <darrell@oak.cse.ucsc.edu> wrote:
>I was looking through Bruce's book yesterday, and I noticed a reference (but no
>details) of a low exponent attack on RSA.  SInce PGP using a small public
>exponent, is it vulnerable to this attack?

This is one of the errors in the book.  It is true only if messages are not
hashed before encryption, which they are in PGP and most any other real
system.

